data.title: Varied Menu, Good Quality, Nice Ambience at Bistro 33 Davis
data.text: We chose Bistro 33 Davis for a nice casual dinner prior to a concert at the excellent Mondavi Center nearby.  We're glad we did.  The menu was varied, prices reasonable, the space inside and out inviting.  Recommended.

data.title: Great Food, lovely pet friendly patio
data.text: Definitely would dine here again, patio is lovely with heaters at night, varied menu and beverage list.  Staff was attentive and patio is pet friendly

data.title: Flavorful food and a good selection of craft beers and wines
data.text: There were six of us in our group for dinner.  We shared couple of appetizers---a crab dip and the seafood "cigars".  Both excellent, especially with the craft India pale ale I chose.  For a main course we had a variety from seafood to meat loaf.  The fish tacos and the Poke Ahi Tuna were favorites.  Three desserts were shared and all were hit---the house-made doughnuts with dipping sauces (chocolate was a favorite here), chocolate cake, and a creme brule.  Service was excellent and suggestions were available when the server was asked.  Everybody left full and happy.

data.title: Great food and atmosphere
data.text: I went here two times during my trip to Davis recently. Once at night just for drinks and then during the day for lunch. At night this place has everything you need from a nice bar inside with tvs, ping pong tables, and great drinks to an outside patio with plenty of seating and fire pits. During the day you can eat outside on the large patio or inside at the bar. I was amazed at how good the food was. I got the fish tacos and my buddy got a seafood sandwich and they were both top notch. I would highly recommend this place when in town.

data.title: Sports bar in the back?
data.text: We went here for dinner and since there was a wait for a table they suggested we sit in their sports bar.   The bar was a dark back room with some tvs on the wall.  They said to order from the bar the full menu.  The bartenders were not too interested in the tables and so service was marginal.  They started playing loud music so we were not sure if they want this area to be a sports bar or a regular bar.  Food was ok.  The dining room and outdoor area are much nicer if you dine here

data.title: Losing its touch with new chef
data.text: Bistro is kind of a go to in Davis for hip fare for the middle-aged (but pretending they are not) crowd. We have been going there since it opened and have usually been satisfied. However, we found out last night that maybe we should be more discerning. The new chef has dropped one of only two vegetarian options (the Pike Market panini) and the remaining one (mushroom ravioli) was bland (but had potential). The cross-cut fries  with gorgonzola sauce are usually pretty crisp, but this time they were limp, though tasty. The onion soup gratinee was pretty, but sweet, a fatal flaw with that item. So, if you have been here before, expect a gastronomic downturn if you go back, and if you are a Bistro newbie, maybe consider somewhere else.

data.title: Yummy Food!!
data.text: The food and cocktails are wonderful. We have had lunch and breakfast. Both meals were great. The Moscow mules were my fave drink.

data.title: Good food, hit n miss service
data.text: I really enjoy the patio seating on a nice afternoon.  The food is always good, but the service is hit and miss.  At times, the service has been great.  Other times, we have had to wait forever to get our drinks, and have had to flag down our server to take our order or get our bill.

data.title: Disappointing Sunday Brunch
data.text: We reserved a table outside for 7 this past Sunday.  The atmosphere was nice and the weather cooperated.  Umbrellas helped.  We gave our drink and brunch orders fairly quickly and the drinks were refilled regularly.  The problem for me was how long it took to get our food.  It took over 45 minutes from our order to finally receiving our order after asking.  I almost had the impression that it was sitting there and if we hadn't asked, we would not have gotten it.  I ordered an omelette and asked for some salad rather than potatoes and toast.  The omelette was OK but the salad was 90% chard which was not what I would have expected as the main green.  It is pretty tough.  When the bill came, I was going to deduct some from the tip due to the delays and my salad, but found an automatic 18% gratuity added.  That really made me upset.  Needless to say, I will not be going back.

data.title: Awful Service - Mediocre Food
data.text:
On a quiet Sunday morning the restaurant was largely empty but it took 20 minutes to get seated. Once we were seated the waiter did not come by our table for another 20 minutes. It was only then we could ask for water. 

Our order was simple, we had already been there 40 minutes so we asked to order right away. Simple order, two cinnamon roles, a fruit plate, and a breakfast panini. They brought our water but nothing else for another 45 minutes. Finally I got so fed up I went looking for our waiter to ask him to check on our order.

5 minutes later another server brought out two cold cinnamon roles, a warm plate of fruit, and a room temperature panini. Clearly our orders had been sitting in the kitchen for quite some time. We had to ask to have one of the hard cold rolls warmed up. My daughter choked down the other cold cinnamon roll.

The fruit platter was small and mediocre. The small wedge of pineapple was so hard it was inedible. The panini was dry and tasteless. The warmed up cinnamon roll was the best thing we ordered.

We left quickly, 2 hours after we walked in. We left without one person apologizing for making us wait for 1 hour & 20 minutes before we were served. That was the most unprofessional restaurant service I have ever experienced.

data.title: Very good food
data.text: The food was very good, but a little on the pricey side. For the price you get great service and very tasteful food. Great ambiance inside or sit outside by a beautiful fire pit.

data.title: Expensive, but great food
data.text: One of the more expensive places I've eaten at in Davis, but a favorite.  Casual atmosphere, and the outdoor dining is really nice (weather and crowds permitting).  The menu ranges from casual sandwiches to very nice entrees.  Wait staff is very friendly.  Definitely get a reservation if it's going to be an event weekend at UC Davis!

data.title: Lunch on the Patio
data.text: I love sitting on the patio and watching people go by.  This place has a really interesting menu and I often get the small plates and a glass of wine to go with.  Portions are generous and the wines are good.

data.title: Good food, good Ambiance, very expensive!!
data.text: I like the food, and I love the location and decorations, but they price their food at least 30% above where it should be for the quality, and at least 50% above where it should be for the quantity offered.

data.title: Ok, but nothing to write home about
data.text: The food is C+ ... occasional good happy hour deals at the bar. The adjacent City Hall Tavern has more reliable staff.

data.title: Slow service and so so food
data.text: The best part about Bistro is sitting outside on a warm night. The worst part is the slow service and unpredictable food.

data.title: Lousy food for price!
data.text:
I took my guest from Hungary to this restaurant as my previous experience for lunch was good. 
Food no very good - we ordered the Butcher Steak - meat was tough and flavorless!
Sea food club sandwich - it was prety much a crab cake. could not find the shrimp or the avocado - both described in the menu.
Clam chowder - awful taste.

data.title: Clunky
data.text: We tried the Eggs Benedict but instead of Canadian bacon a giant slab of ham was included in the dish. I like big slabs of ham, but not in an Eggs Benedict. It seems to be very difficult to find and honest Eggs Benedict in Davis. It's a little like screwing up the Star Bangled Banner, don't ham it up, just learn it and sing it. Don't ham up the Eggs Benedict, just cook it and serve it.

data.title: No-one in my party liked their food, and it was too hot there.
data.text: We were seated upstairs on a 100 degree day.  There didn't seem to be any A/C so it was boiling.  My ahi tuna poke entree was tasty but roughly the size of a fist, which, for an expensive entree consisting mostly of tomatoes, was somewhat ridiculous.  I left feeling starving.  Another person in my party had a steak and said it was terrible. Another person had fish and chips, but said the fish tasted reconstituted rather than real. Disappointing.

data.title: Food just ok, service was terrible
data.text: Been there twice and each time I had poor service.  Food was just ok, so now I will only go there just to see if things have changed,  Lots of outdoor eating, so not really good for hot summer months unless you go early or late in the day.
